WEBVTT

1
00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:21.850
Previously on from...

2
00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:23.956
We need to figure out

3
00:00:23.980 --> 00:00:25.046
where you're gonna live from now on.

4
00:00:25.070 --> 00:00:26.610
I don't think she's a bad person.

5
00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:29.256
If it's all right. she would like to live here.

6
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.506
- With you.
- Okay. Sure.

7
00:00:35.330 --> 00:00:38.976
Abby! Stop! No. no!

8
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.670
Hey. Abbs. I could really use some help.

9
00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:45.646
No! Hey! Hey!

10
00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:49.566
Elgin. I don't want to hate you.

11
00:00:49.590 --> 00:00:51.906
This place took advantage of both of us.

12
00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:55.036
There's something I need your help with.

13
00:00:55.060 --> 00:00:56.786
I think we're gonna need a little bit more.

14
00:00:56.810 --> 00:00:59.786
So. you just... walk inside?

15
00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:02.126
Then I find my dad.
Ethan called it story walking.

16
00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:03.836
He learned about it
from one of his books.

17
00:01:03.860 --> 00:01:05.626
and all his books are
under the house now.

18
00:01:05.650 --> 00:01:07.546
Shit!

19
00:01:07.570 --> 00:01:08.836
I see the bag.

20
00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:10.126
What are the titles?

21
00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:12.506
"Grand gooligog." "the cromenockle."

22
00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.216
Jade. tell me you got something.

23
00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:16.596
The best thing I can do is just find a way

24
00:01:16.620 --> 00:01:19.056
to unlock whatever's locked in here.

25
00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:21.556
Henry said Miranda
started seeing this place

26
00:01:21.580 --> 00:01:23.606
after an acid trip they took.

27
00:01:23.630 --> 00:01:26.340
If it worked for her. it stands
to reason it could work for me.

28
00:01:28.010 --> 00:01:30.776
The night we arrived
here. you had a dream.

29
00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:32.526
- Lake of tears?
- It's here.

30
00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:34.576
And I need you to find it.

31
00:01:34.600 --> 00:01:36.406
- Maybe Jade can help.
- Jade?

32
00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:37.946
The lake of what?

33
00:01:37.970 --> 00:01:39.906
Why were you meditating?

34
00:01:39.930 --> 00:01:42.326
Trying to remember
something that I used to know.

35
00:01:42.350 --> 00:01:44.020
Hey. Victor. we got a lake to find.

36
00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:48.586
Victor!

37
00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:50.360
Hey. talk to me. son.

38
00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:55.080
I told myself it wasn't real.
I told myself it wasn't real.

39
00:01:59.450 --> 00:02:06.266
My wife. Miranda. she
painted things she saw here.

40
00:02:06.290 --> 00:02:09.566
One of those paintings
was of a man in a yellow suit.

41
00:02:09.590 --> 00:02:13.696
You're telling me this
could be the same suit?

42
00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:15.906
You don't see a lot of
people walking around here

43
00:02:15.930 --> 00:02:17.406
in a canary yellow suit.

44
00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:18.906
Well. Victor obviously recognized it.

45
00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:20.366
He didn't just recognize it.

46
00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:22.076
I watched a grown man wet his pants.

47
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:24.326
My question is. if the suit's here.

48
00:02:24.350 --> 00:02:27.036
then where's the guy who wore it?

49
00:02:27.060 --> 00:02:28.206
Long gone. maybe.

50
00:02:28.230 --> 00:02:29.916
For all we know. the
suit might have been

51
00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:31.756
laying out there in the forest for years.

52
00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:33.336
This close to town?

53
00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:34.636
It's not like it's easy to miss.

54
00:02:34.660 --> 00:02:36.296
Then. maybe those
things that come out at night

55
00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:37.756
left it there to mess with our heads.

56
00:02:37.780 --> 00:02:40.216
- Come on.
- The point is. we don't know.

57
00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:42.386
The best thing we can do
right now is talk to Victor.

58
00:02:42.410 --> 00:02:44.096
I'll... I'll do it. I'll talk to him.

59
00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:49.276
No. maybe we should
all... I... I will talk to my son.

60
00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:50.930
Alone.

61
00:02:52.170 --> 00:02:53.696
Okay.

62
00:02:53.720 --> 00:02:56.100
- If there's nothing else. I'll...
- Yeah. no. - Okay.

63
00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:02.826
The young boy. the one dressed in white.

64
00:03:02.850 --> 00:03:07.326
he said to us that we're
running out of time.

65
00:03:07.350 --> 00:03:09.586
For 40 years.

66
00:03:09.610 --> 00:03:12.876
that boy was nothing but
a painting in my basement.

67
00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:16.006
That suit. this place.

68
00:03:16.030 --> 00:03:18.320
all just paintings in the
basement. And now...

69
00:03:22.540 --> 00:03:24.676
I think there was a part of me

70
00:03:24.700 --> 00:03:28.460
that was still trying to
pretend any of this was normal.

71
00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:39.866
Does he know? About his wife?

72
00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:40.890
About you?

73
00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:45.116
We don't even know if it's real.

74
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:47.206
It's real.

75
00:03:47.230 --> 00:03:49.336
No. No. Tabitha's right.

76
00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:51.796
We need to be pretty goddamn sure.

77
00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:54.296
Have you said anything to Fatima?

78
00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:56.086
Nah. she's dealing with enough as is.

79
00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:58.636
All right. then everyone who
knows is standing in this room.

80
00:03:58.660 --> 00:04:01.756
Let's keep it that way
for now. Understood?

81
00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:02.966
Yeah.

82
00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:04.766
The man in the yellow suit.

83
00:04:04.790 --> 00:04:06.686
if Miranda was able to paint him.

84
00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:08.436
that means. somewhere in your mind.

85
00:04:08.460 --> 00:04:10.306
there might be an answer to who he is.

86
00:04:10.330 --> 00:04:13.436
If this is about your
fucking mushrooms...

87
00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:17.276
Boyd. are you seriously okay
with him taking magic mushrooms

88
00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.566
that he found in a haunted forest?

89
00:04:19.590 --> 00:04:21.866
No. Donna. I'm not.

90
00:04:21.890 --> 00:04:24.156
I'm also not okay with
waking up every morning

91
00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:26.496
and counting how many
new bodies there are.

92
00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:29.786
Are you okay with that?
We're losing. Okay?

93
00:04:29.810 --> 00:04:31.126
I'm not gonna say that out there.

94
00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:37.466
but in here. whatever
game this is. we are losing.

95
00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:39.216
And then that freaky
little kid in white pops up

96
00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:41.846
and tells Tabitha that
we're running out of time

97
00:04:41.870 --> 00:04:43.790
and we still don't know
the goddamn rules.

98
00:04:46.750 --> 00:04:49.686
If there are answers in
his head. any answers.

99
00:04:49.710 --> 00:04:52.606
we need to get them out. Okay?

100
00:04:52.630 --> 00:04:54.316
I'll be there with him.

101
00:04:54.340 --> 00:04:56.646
Anything goes wrong. I'm right there.

102
00:04:56.670 --> 00:04:58.526
Well. good luck with that.

103
00:04:58.550 --> 00:05:00.196
Ellis. there are people waiting

104
00:05:00.220 --> 00:05:02.066
to go up to the settlement to gather food.

105
00:05:02.090 --> 00:05:04.010
People still need to eat.

106
00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:11.666
And you. you do this.
you go on this little trip.

107
00:05:11.690 --> 00:05:13.400
you know you may not come back. right?

108
00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:16.280
Yeah.

109
00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:19.966
Come on. Let's go.

110
00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:20.990
Yeah.

111
00:05:26.660 --> 00:05:30.636
Boyd. would you mind
giving us a minute. please?

112
00:05:30.660 --> 00:05:32.596
What? Yeah. Yes. of course.

113
00:05:32.620 --> 00:05:34.460
Of course. Yeah.

114
00:05:48.220 --> 00:05:49.220
Come in.

115
00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:54.536
I hope I didn't wake you.

116
00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:56.296
I didn't sleep much.

117
00:05:56.320 --> 00:05:58.570
Neither did I. at first.

118
00:05:59.570 --> 00:06:05.676
I... I was... Hoping we could talk.

119
00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:06.700
Okay.

120
00:06:15.380 --> 00:06:18.686
I assume... Kenny told you about me?

121
00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:20.356
About what I did?

122
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:21.380
Yeah.

123
00:06:25.180 --> 00:06:27.326
So. why would you want you live here?

124
00:06:27.350 --> 00:06:30.020
Because when I met
you. I knew you were kind.

125
00:06:30.970 --> 00:06:32.616
I know what you did was terrible.

126
00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:34.536
but my father used to always say

127
00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:36.166
that only good people are tortured

128
00:06:36.190 --> 00:06:37.940
by the bad things that they've done.

129
00:06:39.780 --> 00:06:41.916
Plus. I figured here I'd get my own room.

130
00:06:45.320 --> 00:06:47.296
I'll go make us breakfast.

131
00:06:47.320 --> 00:06:48.910
I'll be right down.

132
00:07:28.530 --> 00:07:32.716
No. no. no. no. no! No! Please!

133
00:07:32.740 --> 00:07:33.596
No!

134
00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:34.766
- Sara?
- No!

135
00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:36.726
No. no. no. please!

136
00:07:36.750 --> 00:07:38.516
What's happened?

137
00:09:44.080 --> 00:09:46.066
Why were you in the woods with Ethan?

138
00:09:46.090 --> 00:09:48.566
You should really ask Ethan about that.

139
00:09:48.590 --> 00:09:50.380
I'm asking you.

140
00:09:51.930 --> 00:09:53.600
Did he tell you he saw Jim in the forest?

141
00:09:55.890 --> 00:09:57.036
Yeah.

142
00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:58.326
Well. apparently. Jim told him

143
00:09:58.350 --> 00:10:00.576
that he had to find the lake of tears.

144
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.036
Does that sound familiar?

145
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:03.576
That's not... that's not real.

146
00:10:03.600 --> 00:10:06.336
No. it's not. But it is to him.

147
00:10:06.360 --> 00:10:08.046
I'm not exactly the best person

148
00:10:08.070 --> 00:10:13.886
to be giving advice
about... Well. anything really.

149
00:10:13.910 --> 00:10:17.636
but I do know... Some kids
just feel more comfortable

150
00:10:17.660 --> 00:10:20.516
living in their imagination. Right?

151
00:10:20.540 --> 00:10:22.976
It's where they go when
the world gets scary.

152
00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:26.396
'Cause. sometimes.
believing in impossible things.

153
00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:30.590
it... helps with the...

154
00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:32.920
It just helps.

155
00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:41.600
I'm sorry about what I said in the barn.

156
00:10:42.980 --> 00:10:44.900
Don't be.

157
00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:47.900
You weren't wrong.

158
00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:55.950
Be careful with those.

159
00:11:02.830 --> 00:11:05.266
Everything all right?

160
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:07.686
If you can tell me the last
time everything was all right.

161
00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:08.896
you win a cookie.

162
00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:10.670
Are you ready for this?

163
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:14.260
Fuck no.

164
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:22.100
Ethan?

165
00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:34.466
Dad?

166
00:11:34.490 --> 00:11:36.490
Can you hear me?

167
00:11:37.740 --> 00:11:40.256
Please. answer me.

168
00:11:40.280 --> 00:11:42.306
Dad.

169
00:11:44.080 --> 00:11:45.330
Yeah?

170
00:11:59.640 --> 00:12:01.890
Why didn't you tell me
about the lake of tears?

171
00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:06.930
Why did you go to Jade and
Victor and not come to me?

172
00:12:08.770 --> 00:12:10.586
Ethan.

173
00:12:10.610 --> 00:12:12.570
I need you to talk to me. please.

174
00:12:19.160 --> 00:12:21.790
I didn't tell you because I
knew you wouldn't believe me.

175
00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:29.646
He told me I need to find it.

176
00:12:29.670 --> 00:12:30.710
He told me.

177
00:12:32.840 --> 00:12:36.640
And when I find it.
that'll prove it was real.

178
00:12:38.970 --> 00:12:42.470
He's not gone. He's still here.

179
00:12:51.900 --> 00:12:53.706
Okay. then.

180
00:12:53.730 --> 00:12:55.650
I need you to pack a bag.

181
00:12:56.690 --> 00:12:57.756
Why?

182
00:12:57.780 --> 00:12:59.820
We're going on a trip.

183
00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:11.856
You find anything?

184
00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:13.936
No. they're kids' books. Julie.

185
00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:15.356
If you don't wanna help
me. I can do this on my own.

186
00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:16.986
I'm not saying that.

187
00:13:17.010 --> 00:13:18.350
I just...

188
00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:25.576
What?

189
00:13:25.600 --> 00:13:27.440
Storywalker Fred.

190
00:13:29.980 --> 00:13:31.666
Who?

191
00:13:31.690 --> 00:13:33.456
Who's that?

192
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:37.546
He's the distant cousin
of the grand gooligog.

193
00:13:37.570 --> 00:13:39.506
Here we are.

194
00:13:39.530 --> 00:13:41.376
"Storywalker Fred was
an elevator repairman

195
00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:43.596
who spent his weekends
story walking as he pleased

196
00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:45.386
through all the wondrous tales

197
00:13:45.410 --> 00:13:47.926
and greatest adventures of our time."

198
00:13:47.950 --> 00:13:49.426
Julie?

199
00:13:49.450 --> 00:13:51.226
Hide the books.

200
00:13:51.250 --> 00:13:53.090
Yeah. We're in here!

201
00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:58.816
I need you to pack your bag.

202
00:13:58.840 --> 00:14:00.696
We're going out to the settlement.

203
00:14:00.720 --> 00:14:02.406
Why?

204
00:14:02.430 --> 00:14:05.680
Ethan's convinced he
needs to find that lake of tears.

205
00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:08.286
The magic lake he used to talk about?

206
00:14:08.310 --> 00:14:09.310
Yeah.

207
00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:11.916
He said he saw your father.

208
00:14:11.940 --> 00:14:15.536
and then your dad asked him to find it.

209
00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:18.256
He... he saw him?

210
00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:21.006
- What does that mean?
- I don't know.

211
00:14:21.030 --> 00:14:22.030
I think he's grieving.

212
00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:25.926
What I do know is
that. if I try to stop him.

213
00:14:25.950 --> 00:14:29.000
then he'll sneak out
and look for it by himself.

214
00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:32.950
This way. I can keep him safe.

215
00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:35.540
Okay.

216
00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:38.436
So. what do you need me for?

217
00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.816
Well. you're not staying here alone.

218
00:14:40.840 --> 00:14:43.406
I'm not gonna be
alone. I'll be with Randall.

219
00:14:43.430 --> 00:14:46.576
- Randall.
- Mom. it's not like that.

220
00:14:46.600 --> 00:14:47.680
It's really not.

221
00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:51.310
I'll stay at the clinic. Kristi
and marielle are there.

222
00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:56.036
Can I talk to you for a minute?

223
00:14:56.060 --> 00:14:57.770
- Mom!
- It's okay.

224
00:15:08.530 --> 00:15:10.386
Look. first of all. I just wanna say sorry...

225
00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.476
no. no. no. Stop talking. Just listen.

226
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:13.846
Okay.

227
00:15:13.870 --> 00:15:15.646
I don't know you. Randall.

228
00:15:15.670 --> 00:15:17.516
I don't know who you
are or what you want.

229
00:15:17.540 --> 00:15:19.226
Julie trusts you.

230
00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:21.986
She feels safe around you.
and she needs that right now.

231
00:15:22.010 --> 00:15:24.146
So. I need you to look
me in the eye and tell me

232
00:15:24.170 --> 00:15:26.816
you understand what I will do to you

233
00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:28.680
if you ever do anything
to break that trust.

234
00:15:30.010 --> 00:15:31.090
I understand.

235
00:15:32.220 --> 00:15:33.350
Okay. good.

236
00:15:34.850 --> 00:15:36.326
Mom.

237
00:15:36.350 --> 00:15:38.376
Honey.

238
00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:39.740
What?

239
00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:42.780
- I love you.
- And I love you. too.

240
00:15:44.320 --> 00:15:46.296
- Promise me you'll be okay.
- I promise.

241
00:15:46.320 --> 00:15:47.490
Yeah.

242
00:15:49.200 --> 00:15:50.676
I'll be back tomorrow.

243
00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:51.910
Yeah.

244
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:56.226
This is your water.

245
00:15:56.250 --> 00:15:57.846
Look. I don't need to go.

246
00:15:57.870 --> 00:15:59.606
Ellis. it's your turn.

247
00:15:59.630 --> 00:16:02.260
Yeah. but I'm sure Donna can
find someone to take my place.

248
00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:05.196
I'm fine.

249
00:16:05.220 --> 00:16:07.156
And Donna needs people out there

250
00:16:07.180 --> 00:16:09.180
that she knows she can rely on.

251
00:16:10.760 --> 00:16:12.850
Honey. I'm okay. I promise.

252
00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:15.640
Yeah.

253
00:16:16.730 --> 00:16:17.730
Okay.

254
00:16:18.810 --> 00:16:19.810
Okay.

255
00:16:22.020 --> 00:16:24.876
Tommy is responsible
for the cans on the door.

256
00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:27.176
Ella and Jordan will check the windows.

257
00:16:27.200 --> 00:16:29.836
and then about 20 minutes
or so before sundown...

258
00:16:29.860 --> 00:16:32.756
do a headcount. I know. I got it.

259
00:16:32.780 --> 00:16:38.346
Just. keep an eye on
Fatima. with Ellis gone.

260
00:16:38.370 --> 00:16:39.726
Yeah. I got it.

261
00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:40.726
Yup.

262
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:42.000
- Donna?
- Okay.

263
00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:44.670
Do you have room for two more?

264
00:16:46.300 --> 00:16:47.550
More the merrier.

265
00:16:51.850 --> 00:16:55.656
Okay. let's. move it out.

266
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:57.100
Come on.

267
00:16:58.310 --> 00:16:59.310
Let's go!

268
00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:28.776
How's this?

269
00:17:28.800 --> 00:17:31.986
This is. perfect. Thank you. Elgin.

270
00:17:32.010 --> 00:17:34.696
I can help you with the rest.
if you tell me what this is for.

271
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:35.890
The rest I have to do myself.

272
00:17:37.470 --> 00:17:38.890
You should go now.

273
00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:41.480
Okay.

274
00:17:51.280 --> 00:17:53.636
Victor. Hey.

275
00:17:53.660 --> 00:17:58.596
Three. four... What are you doing?

276
00:17:58.620 --> 00:18:00.976
I have to see if the trees have moved.

277
00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.516
Why... why would the trees be moving?

278
00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:05.146
Because everything is changing.

279
00:18:05.170 --> 00:18:08.226
and first it was snowing.
and now everything's green.

280
00:18:08.250 --> 00:18:09.936
and everything is just moving too fast.

281
00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:12.446
And I-I used to measure
all the time. and...

282
00:18:12.470 --> 00:18:14.906
and then I haven't been paying attention.

283
00:18:14.930 --> 00:18:17.656
and I should have been paying attention.

284
00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:20.156
I should have been paying attention.

285
00:18:20.180 --> 00:18:21.180
Measure...

286
00:18:26.360 --> 00:18:27.740
Can I help?

287
00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:30.860
See if the trees are moving?

288
00:18:37.870 --> 00:18:39.250
Okay.

289
00:18:40.540 --> 00:18:42.460
Okay. what do I do?

290
00:18:45.670 --> 00:18:49.186
You start with this leg like this.

291
00:18:49.210 --> 00:18:52.196
- One.
- One.

292
00:18:52.220 --> 00:18:53.526
Two.

293
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:32.800
What the fuck?

294
00:19:45.890 --> 00:19:46.890
Hi.

295
00:20:18.130 --> 00:20:19.986
You know what they used
to call me in the army. right?

296
00:20:20.010 --> 00:20:21.490
- Mr. Fish and loaves!
- That's right!

297
00:20:55.630 --> 00:20:56.760
Hi.

298
00:20:59.380 --> 00:21:00.510
Boyd!

299
00:21:01.640 --> 00:21:03.826
What's going on?

300
00:21:03.850 --> 00:21:06.866
Is Kenny in this room right now?

301
00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:09.576
Wha...?

302
00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:10.916
Yes.

303
00:21:10.940 --> 00:21:11.980
Never mind then.

304
00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:14.876
Is he on...?

305
00:21:14.900 --> 00:21:16.820
Mushrooms he found in the woods.

306
00:21:18.030 --> 00:21:18.966
Right.

307
00:21:18.990 --> 00:21:21.256
You need something?

308
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.870
It's Fatima.

309
00:21:24.030 --> 00:21:26.410
I think maybe you should
come up to the colony house.

310
00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:38.646
I should go.

311
00:21:38.670 --> 00:21:40.710
No. Stay?

312
00:21:42.640 --> 00:21:43.680
Please.

313
00:21:46.720 --> 00:21:48.220
Okay.

314
00:21:51.390 --> 00:21:54.180
You remember this is
the first place I met you.

315
00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:58.360
It's funny how things change.

316
00:22:05.030 --> 00:22:06.870
Do you still see her?

317
00:22:08.870 --> 00:22:11.000
The woman in the kimono?

318
00:22:12.330 --> 00:22:14.516
No.

319
00:22:14.540 --> 00:22:17.146
Do you think it's because
you did what she asked.

320
00:22:17.170 --> 00:22:19.736
so. now. she leaves you alone?

321
00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:22.656
Sara. is something going on?

322
00:22:25.930 --> 00:22:28.946
I thought for a while

323
00:22:28.970 --> 00:22:31.326
that the voices were leaving me alone.

324
00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:33.166
I thought they were done with me.

325
00:22:33.190 --> 00:22:36.070
but turns out... They're not.

326
00:22:38.230 --> 00:22:41.336
And what do they want you to do?

327
00:22:41.360 --> 00:22:43.336
It doesn't make any sense.

328
00:22:43.360 --> 00:22:46.006
They said they want
me to go to the diner.

329
00:22:46.030 --> 00:22:47.990
pour a glass of water from the pitcher...

330
00:22:50.370 --> 00:22:53.210
Take a sip. and then pour it back in.

331
00:22:54.540 --> 00:22:56.460
And then what?

332
00:22:57.590 --> 00:22:58.630
That's it.

333
00:23:02.380 --> 00:23:04.776
So. how's... how's that
gonna hurt anyone?

334
00:23:04.800 --> 00:23:06.526
I don't know.

335
00:23:06.550 --> 00:23:09.656
But there's always a consequence.

336
00:23:09.680 --> 00:23:11.680
Sara. it's just water.

337
00:23:12.730 --> 00:23:14.440
- But I'll have drank from it.
- So?

338
00:23:17.730 --> 00:23:20.626
Whatever is wrong with me.

339
00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:24.586
what if it's like an infection?

340
00:23:24.610 --> 00:23:26.546
What if I pass it on to someone else

341
00:23:26.570 --> 00:23:28.636
and then the voices start torturing them?

342
00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:32.210
I don't want anyone
to have to live like this.

343
00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:35.000
Okay.

344
00:23:37.420 --> 00:23:38.686
What if you just don't do it?

345
00:23:38.710 --> 00:23:41.476
They said. if I don't do it by midday.

346
00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:45.236
then something bad will happen
to someone that I care about.

347
00:23:45.260 --> 00:23:49.616
and it will keep happening until I do it.

348
00:23:58.060 --> 00:23:59.836
How many steps?

349
00:23:59.860 --> 00:24:01.400
23?

350
00:24:08.950 --> 00:24:12.516
Victor. I want to talk to you
about what happened yesterday.

351
00:24:12.540 --> 00:24:14.136
Nothing happened yesterday.

352
00:24:14.160 --> 00:24:15.886
Victor. can we...

353
00:24:15.910 --> 00:24:18.516
no. dad. you can't... you
can't just stop in the middle.

354
00:24:18.540 --> 00:24:23.396
'cause you'll... you'll mess everything up.

355
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:28.260
I'm sorry. but I need you to talk to me.

356
00:24:29.470 --> 00:24:31.656
Whatever it was.

357
00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:35.196
whatever you're afraid
of. you can tell me.

358
00:24:35.220 --> 00:24:37.166
Well. it's... I think the tree...

359
00:24:37.190 --> 00:24:39.536
I think they moved a little.

360
00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:43.480
You said that you told
yourself it wasn't real.

361
00:24:45.780 --> 00:24:47.740
Did you mean the yellow suit?

362
00:24:52.410 --> 00:24:54.886
C-Can you tell me about
the man who wore it?

363
00:24:54.910 --> 00:24:59.556
Did... was he someone
that hurt... hurt you?

364
00:25:06.550 --> 00:25:12.196
Look. Victor. please. whatever it is.

365
00:25:12.220 --> 00:25:14.760
we'll face it together. You can tell me.

366
00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:23.876
Victor. what... Victor!

367
00:25:23.900 --> 00:25:25.860
Come. Come with me and I'll show you.

368
00:25:30.990 --> 00:25:35.676
Hey. Just sit down
and don't go anywhere.

369
00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:36.950
Come on.

370
00:25:40.750 --> 00:25:42.710
Come in.

371
00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:52.026
I told Kenny not to bother you.

372
00:25:52.050 --> 00:25:53.390
Yeah.

373
00:25:55.760 --> 00:25:57.550
Well. he...

374
00:26:00.940 --> 00:26:02.320
It's a lotta dirt.

375
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:04.520
Yeah.

376
00:26:06.230 --> 00:26:07.860
You wanna tell me what's going on?

377
00:26:10.280 --> 00:26:11.530
I'm making a monster.

378
00:26:14.410 --> 00:26:16.216
Here we go. "The grand gooligog

379
00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:18.176
asks Fred about story walking.

380
00:26:18.200 --> 00:26:20.426
'How do you choose a point
in the story you wish to see?'"

381
00:26:20.450 --> 00:26:21.936
and?

382
00:26:21.960 --> 00:26:24.396
"Fred replied. 'you have
to create a bookmark.'

383
00:26:24.420 --> 00:26:26.186
Fred discovered that
by leaving a bookmark

384
00:26:26.210 --> 00:26:27.896
somewhere in the story. he could choose

385
00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:30.356
whatever chapter he wished to visit."

386
00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:32.946
We have to make a bookmark.

387
00:26:32.970 --> 00:26:34.736
Julie. that doesn't make any sense.

388
00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:36.116
I know what you're gonna say.

389
00:26:36.140 --> 00:26:38.326
This is a kid's book and it's crazy.

390
00:26:38.350 --> 00:26:39.520
That's 'cause it is.

391
00:26:41.930 --> 00:26:43.956
What if that's not the
right way to look at this?

392
00:26:43.980 --> 00:26:46.286
What if story walking existed here first?

393
00:26:46.310 --> 00:26:48.246
The fuck you talking about?

394
00:26:48.270 --> 00:26:52.716
Everything here is impossible. Okay?

395
00:26:52.740 --> 00:26:54.136
But it's also real.

396
00:26:54.160 --> 00:26:56.636
We're here. right now.
in this impossible place.

397
00:26:56.660 --> 00:26:58.926
What if all of the crazy
shit that happens here.

398
00:26:58.950 --> 00:27:03.710
has been... like. seeping out into...

399
00:27:08.130 --> 00:27:10.686
My mom. My mom had
nightmares about this place

400
00:27:10.710 --> 00:27:12.736
when she was a little
girl. She didn't realize

401
00:27:12.760 --> 00:27:15.606
that she was dreaming about
it then. but she was. Okay?

402
00:27:15.630 --> 00:27:17.906
Who knows how many
other kids or adults

403
00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:19.786
or fucking children's book authors

404
00:27:19.810 --> 00:27:22.156
have had dreams about
this place without knowing it?

405
00:27:22.180 --> 00:27:24.456
And what if this author had a dream

406
00:27:24.480 --> 00:27:26.496
about someone like
me doing what I can do.

407
00:27:26.520 --> 00:27:28.786
he woke up. wrote it down
and called it story walking?

408
00:27:28.810 --> 00:27:31.456
But there's literally thousands of books

409
00:27:31.480 --> 00:27:33.006
that have stories and rules
about traveling through time.

410
00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:34.086
No. no!

411
00:27:34.110 --> 00:27:35.466
Why would this book.

412
00:27:35.490 --> 00:27:37.386
the one with fucking
Fred the story walker.

413
00:27:37.410 --> 00:27:39.636
why would this book be the
one that explains anything?

414
00:27:39.660 --> 00:27:41.306
Because. out of all those books.

415
00:27:41.330 --> 00:27:43.556
this is the one my brother had
with him when we came here.

416
00:27:43.580 --> 00:27:46.056
Okay? And maybe
that means something.

417
00:27:47.580 --> 00:27:50.396
Maybe it's fate. I... Fate.

418
00:27:50.420 --> 00:27:52.026
Randall. if I'm right.

419
00:27:52.050 --> 00:27:54.106
this could actually be
an instruction manual

420
00:27:54.130 --> 00:27:58.680
on how to save my
dad. and it's all I have.

421
00:28:01.060 --> 00:28:02.900
So. I'm gonna try.
whether you help me or not.

422
00:28:07.480 --> 00:28:09.360
So. what kind of bookmark do we need?

423
00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:13.336
When you say 'monster'...?

424
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:16.086
Boyd. I know you're worried about me.

425
00:28:16.110 --> 00:28:18.006
but you don't have to be.

426
00:28:18.030 --> 00:28:20.426
Yeah. yeah. yeah. I hear you saying that.

427
00:28:20.450 --> 00:28:25.620
The problem is. Fatima.
this says something else.

428
00:28:26.750 --> 00:28:29.516
Have you told Ellis what
you're doing in here?

429
00:28:29.540 --> 00:28:32.186
I wasn't trying to hide it from him.

430
00:28:32.210 --> 00:28:33.920
He... he has been so worried lately.

431
00:28:35.590 --> 00:28:38.486
I figured once he was
back from the food run.

432
00:28:38.510 --> 00:28:40.026
once he could see what I was doing.

433
00:28:40.050 --> 00:28:42.026
it would be easier to explain.

434
00:28:42.050 --> 00:28:43.140
Okay. great.

435
00:28:44.270 --> 00:28:46.400
Explain it to me?

436
00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:56.876
Where I grew up. beliefs were very rigid.

437
00:28:56.900 --> 00:28:59.296
They defined you.

438
00:28:59.320 --> 00:29:02.806
But my dad told stories
of all the different faiths.

439
00:29:02.830 --> 00:29:04.596
It used to drive my mother crazy

440
00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:07.580
because she understood
how dangerous it was.

441
00:29:08.660 --> 00:29:11.856
But he would just smile.

442
00:29:11.880 --> 00:29:16.646
He'd say. "Fatima. they have it wrong.

443
00:29:16.670 --> 00:29:19.486
They all think their road is the only way.

444
00:29:19.510 --> 00:29:23.236
Don't they understand that
all roads lead to the divine?

445
00:29:23.260 --> 00:29:25.996
They simply take
different paths to get there."

446
00:29:26.020 --> 00:29:31.416
Fatima... Of all the
stories my father would tell.

447
00:29:31.440 --> 00:29:35.496
all the fables and myths...

448
00:29:35.520 --> 00:29:39.070
there's one story I've been
thinking a lot about lately.

449
00:29:41.240 --> 00:29:44.700
Do you know what a golem is. Boyd?

450
00:29:56.670 --> 00:29:58.436
Well?

451
00:29:58.460 --> 00:30:00.340
She's...

452
00:30:02.890 --> 00:30:05.196
She's making a golem.

453
00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:06.486
A what?

454
00:30:06.510 --> 00:30:09.680
It's a part of a religious folklore.

455
00:30:11.020 --> 00:30:13.286
It's a giant made of Clay.

456
00:30:13.310 --> 00:30:15.996
It protects people. It's a champion.

457
00:30:16.020 --> 00:30:18.810
She said it's a symbol of hope.

458
00:30:22.150 --> 00:30:25.046
Maybe. for now. we
just give her some space.

459
00:30:25.070 --> 00:30:27.200
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
That's your solution. is...

460
00:30:29.080 --> 00:30:30.676
Give her some space?

461
00:30:30.700 --> 00:30:32.226
She's not hurting anybody.

462
00:30:32.250 --> 00:30:33.766
That's not the point.

463
00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:36.266
We have both seen
this place turn people.

464
00:30:36.290 --> 00:30:39.896
change them little by little. until. one day.

465
00:30:39.920 --> 00:30:41.550
we turn around and...

466
00:30:43.260 --> 00:30:46.310
And the person that...
We knew is... is gone.

467
00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:54.826
Boyd. that person up there
is not the Fatima that I know.

468
00:30:54.850 --> 00:30:57.086
And I think if you're
being honest with yourself.

469
00:30:57.110 --> 00:30:58.990
that's not the Fatima you know either.

470
00:31:09.030 --> 00:31:11.096
Can I ask you something?

471
00:31:11.120 --> 00:31:12.370
Yeah.

472
00:31:13.870 --> 00:31:15.710
What the hell are you doing out here?

473
00:31:18.290 --> 00:31:19.670
I don't know.

474
00:31:21.300 --> 00:31:23.550
I don't know what I'm doing.

475
00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:28.486
I just keep walking around
with this knot of terror inside me

476
00:31:28.510 --> 00:31:31.576
that feels like it's going to explode.

477
00:31:31.600 --> 00:31:34.416
And the whole time.

478
00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:37.780
there's this question and
it keeps ringing in my mind.

479
00:31:40.650 --> 00:31:42.150
What am I supposed to do now?

480
00:31:43.280 --> 00:31:47.320
Jim's gone. and I keep
looking for him. but he's gone.

481
00:31:49.990 --> 00:31:53.910
I have memories in my head
that belong to other people.

482
00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:58.016
Memories that might have
answers. but I'm terrified

483
00:31:58.040 --> 00:32:00.266
of what it'll cost if...

484
00:32:00.290 --> 00:32:03.460
if I go too far or if I remember too much.

485
00:32:05.220 --> 00:32:06.640
But if I don't...

486
00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:16.140
I know I'm failing.

487
00:32:17.690 --> 00:32:19.496
What's gonna happen
when Ethan learns

488
00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:23.796
that the lake of tears is not real?

489
00:32:23.820 --> 00:32:25.716
How am I gonna deal with that?

490
00:32:25.740 --> 00:32:27.756
Hey. everyone?

491
00:32:27.780 --> 00:32:29.966
Let's just take a little break. okay?

492
00:32:29.990 --> 00:32:31.176
You good?

493
00:32:31.200 --> 00:32:33.676
Yeah. we're fine. Just.
need a little breather.

494
00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:34.766
Okay.

495
00:32:34.790 --> 00:32:36.170
Let's sit down.

496
00:32:46.050 --> 00:32:48.236
I don't know how to do this alone.

497
00:32:48.260 --> 00:32:50.276
You are not alone.

498
00:32:50.300 --> 00:32:52.026
People keep saying that.

499
00:32:52.050 --> 00:32:54.090
Well. maybe you should fucking listen.

500
00:32:56.680 --> 00:32:58.996
I don't want to find
another one of those notes

501
00:32:59.020 --> 00:33:01.336
like the one on my nightstand.

502
00:33:01.360 --> 00:33:03.706
You are not going to
put me in the position

503
00:33:03.730 --> 00:33:05.796
of having to explain to your kids

504
00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:07.546
why I'm still alive and you're not.

505
00:33:07.570 --> 00:33:09.676
- Donna. I'm...
- no.

506
00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:13.636
You and those kids

507
00:33:13.660 --> 00:33:17.710
are as much my family as
any family I have ever had.

508
00:33:19.330 --> 00:33:22.516
So. from now on.

509
00:33:22.540 --> 00:33:25.186
if anyone is going to risk their lives

510
00:33:25.210 --> 00:33:27.946
to do something stupid...

511
00:33:27.970 --> 00:33:31.390
That person is gonna be me and not you.

512
00:33:33.550 --> 00:33:34.550
We clear on that?

513
00:33:35.970 --> 00:33:38.680
I am asking. are we clear on that?

514
00:33:42.480 --> 00:33:44.956
- We're clear.
- Okay.

515
00:33:44.980 --> 00:33:47.770
Mom! Come look at this!

516
00:33:49.280 --> 00:33:50.360
Come on.

517
00:33:57.370 --> 00:33:59.556
Looks like a broken wing.

518
00:34:01.500 --> 00:34:03.356
Must have fallen from
a nest or something.

519
00:34:03.380 --> 00:34:06.066
We never see anything here but crows.

520
00:34:06.090 --> 00:34:07.476
We have to take him with us.

521
00:34:07.500 --> 00:34:09.170
Ethan...

522
00:34:10.300 --> 00:34:13.430
Mom. this is a sign.

523
00:34:15.300 --> 00:34:16.866
If the lake at the settlement

524
00:34:16.890 --> 00:34:19.906
really is the lake of tears. it'll fix him.

525
00:34:19.930 --> 00:34:22.706
That's how we'll know.

526
00:34:22.730 --> 00:34:25.360
We have to take him with us.

527
00:34:32.400 --> 00:34:35.676
I can't imagine what this is like for her.

528
00:34:35.700 --> 00:34:39.766
At least when I got here.
I found you. you know?

529
00:34:39.790 --> 00:34:42.516
I mean. she lost the
only person she had here.

530
00:34:42.540 --> 00:34:43.540
Yeah.

531
00:34:44.920 --> 00:34:46.516
I can't tell if she's handling it well

532
00:34:46.540 --> 00:34:49.340
